Program: Outlook
Title: 23/02/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0068tyr
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 24 Feb 2010
Margaret Humphreys Margaret has dedicated her life to helping reunite families torn apart by the British government's policy of forcibly sending children thousands of miles from home between the 1920s and 1970s. As the current British Prime Minister apologises for the policy she tells Roger Hearing about her life and work. Zimbabwean wedding plans Steve Vickers hears from Zimbabweans about the difficulties of scraping together a traditional bride price known as a lobola before they can officially tie the knot. Sharona Alperin Roger Hearing speaks to the woman who inspired the song "My Sharona", Los Angeles realtor Sharona Alperin. Show less